column2: an A.M. Eatery////The wait was 30 minutes but worth it depending on what you get. I got the "Benny Duo" which is where you pick two different kinds of Eggs Benedict and they give you one of each. I got the Chilaquiles one which had corn tortilla base with cheese
column4: and a poached egg with hollandaise sauce. The other one was the "Bella Bella Benny" which has prosciutto
column6: and a poached egg with hollandaise sauce and a balsamic glaze. Super good!
